  "text": "It is noteworthy that the AA-binding site in Kv1.1 overlaps very well with the previously reported Kvb1.1-binding site [CITATION_1] ). Zhou et al found that Kvb1.1 binds to the pore-facing residues V551, I554, V558 and V562 of Kv1.4, which are homologous to V505, I508, V512 and V516 of Kv1.5. These residues are lining the inner cavity and consistently they interact with both Kvb1.1 and AA. In addition, block by AA was perturbed by I502 and P513, although these residues are not perfectly facing into the pore. However, as the alkyl chains of AA and AEA are highly flexible an additional interaction with these residues seems plausible.",
